<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1947-10-06T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1947-10-06T00:00:00-05:00" n="672" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d672">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">811.516 Export-Import Bank/10–647:
                            Airgram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                    State</gloss> to the <gloss type="to">Embassy in Mexico</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#left">
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">restricted</hi>
                            </seg>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1947-10-06">October 6,
                                1947</date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>A–770. Credit application for $3.5 million behalf Nueva Compañía
                            Electrica Chapala, <gloss target="#t_SA1">S.A.</gloss>, to finance
                            purchases in U.S. of equipment and materials for Colomilla
                            Hydro-electric Power Plant, <pb facs="0785" n="769" xml:id="pg_769"/>
                            two associated transmission lines, and the pumping station was approved
                            by <gloss target="#t_Eximbank1">Eximbank</gloss> Board of Directors
                            October 1. This is the first specific credit approved under the $50
                            million commitment made to Mexico in April 1947.</p>
                        <p rend="center">. . . . . . .</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Lovett</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>